<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99251189022176></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99251189022176><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99251189022176>RE: About Agility</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99251189022176#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>498 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 14th 5:44 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.47]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Near as I've ever been able to tell, 4 AGI gets you one point of AC.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't know if level affects that - haven't checked it in a while.  The key thing to consider is that it takes a lot of Agi to get a little AC - and even if you burn 15 stat points on Agi you're only getting 4 AC for it.  Considering that at high levels there seems to be a multiplying effect when you equip AC gear (If I equip a AC 7 piece, my AC goes up 10 or 11 - never saw an explanation for it though) the 3 or 4 AC you get from skill points doesn't seem to be a good return on investment here.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
