	   <tr><td colspan=2>It's not too hard to show the marginal effect of AGI with a couple item swaps.&nbsp;&nbsp;Vox Bracers vs. Serp Bracers are probably the best example.  I've never heard anyone seriously advocate Serp over Vox.  Just equip a pair of one vs. a pair of the other.  The AC difference favors the Vox enough that it seems every mid-level monk eventually ends up with a pair.<br><br>Another good example is the old monk footwear favorite Wolf Fur Slippers vs. the new Wu's Slippers.  Wu's has higher AC, but lower AGI.  I was wearing Wolf Fur when the Wu's came out and promptly switched.  Sure do miss the +20 Mana from the Wolf Fur though -- heh heh.<br><br>The reason why Vox Bracers tend to become readily available and cheap (got my pair for 140PP -- great value for the AC) is due to people trying to get the King Gobbo in Perma to drop the White Wolf Cloak.  Lotta bracers for each cloak that drops.  Perma, by the way, is a great place for a monk to go for items, between the Archaolgists Pack, Wolf Fur Slippers (still a decent piece even with the Wu's out), Vox Bracers, White Wolf Cloak, and the Purple Headband quest item Crown of Zaharn.  One reason why monks have tended to prefer SolA seems to be that by the time you can go get these items, you can't get doodly for experience in Perma.  It will be interesting to see how they change the dungeon, as that is the next one Verant is going to 'fix'.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
